          <section id="industry-playbook" class="scroll-mt-24">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-5">8. RFID deployment playbook by industry</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Eight B2B industries account for over 85% of global RFID deployment volume in 2024 (IDTechEx RFID Forecasts, 2024). Each industry has a dominant combination of frequency band, chip family, form factor, and reader strategy that has emerged as the de-facto standard — driven by real-world constraints like wash cycles, metal substrates, line-of-sight workflows, and regulatory compliance. Use the playbook below to jump straight to the proven combination for your vertical, then read the referenced cluster articles for tactical deep-dives.
            </p>
            <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2" data-speakable="industry-playbook">
              <article class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
                <p class="eyebrow-label text-[#0d7377] mb-2">Hospitality</p>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Hotels, resorts, events, theme parks</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                  Dominant stack: <strong>HF 13.56 MHz MIFARE Classic / Plus / DESFire EV3</strong> for door locks plus <strong>UHF EPC Gen2</strong> for cashless wristband payment. 90%+ of branded hotels standardize on MIFARE family because of installed lock compatibility (Saflok, VingCard, Onity, SALTO). Chain-level programs are migrating from Classic to Plus EV2 or DESFire EV3 for AES-128 security, triggered by insurance-carrier cybersecurity audits. Silicone wristbands dominate water parks, fitness resorts, and all-inclusive programs at 15-30% higher per-guest spend vs cash-only operations (Intellitix / RFID Journal, 2024).
                </p>
                <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-[#0d7377]"><a href="/solutions/hotel-access-rfid" class="hover:underline">→ Hotel access solution page</a></p>
