                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                  Dominant stack: <strong>UHF 860-960 MHz Impinj Monza R6-P or NXP UCODE 9</strong> in textile heat-seal tags (hidden in garment seam) at 200+ wash cycles per 85°C / 2.5 g/L NaClO. The three fastest-growing laundry UHF tag segments 2023-2024 are industrial uniform rental, hospital linen under EN 14065 RABC, and hotel linen rotation. TRSA 2024 benchmark: RFID-equipped laundries beat non-RFID peers on 7 of 8 operational KPIs including billing accuracy (+18 points) and shrinkage reduction (14% → 4%). Payback typically 6-14 months.
