                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                  Dominant stack: <strong>UHF EPC Gen2v2 Impinj M730 / M800</strong> inlays embedded in hangtags, care labels, or adhesive stickers. Walmart's 2022 apparel mandate and the EU Digital Product Passport (ESPR 2024/1781) both drive this segment. Decathlon documented inventory accuracy going from 70% to 98% across 1,500+ stores after UHF item-level tagging (GS1, 2023). Unit cost at 1M+ MOQ: $0.04-0.08 per inlay. Retail is by far the highest-volume UHF segment — 42 billion UHF tags shipped globally in 2024 (RAIN Alliance).
