                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                  Dominant stack: <strong>UHF 860-960 MHz Alien Higgs-9 or NXP UCODE DNA</strong> in on-metal or hard-shell housings. Critical differences from retail: logistics tags face metal substrates (containers, pallets, cages), extreme temperature ranges (-40 to +85°C), and years-long deployment cycles. Anti-metal construction is mandatory — standard UHF stickers lose 90-99% read range on steel. GS1 EPC Tag Data Standard 1.13 is the encoding baseline. Fastest-growing subsegment 2024: returnable transit packaging (RTP) tracking at 11% CAGR (ABI Research).
